1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a system for real-time streaming of medical images to head-mounted displays, which involves computer vision techniques for blending the images with the surgical site. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper involves the use of mixed reality visualization, which involves graphics techniques for blending the medical images with the surgical site. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the potential benefits of the proposed system for reducing surgeon load and improving hand-eye coordination, which are relevant to human-computer interaction. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper involves the streaming of high-resolution medical images in real-time, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper does not explicitly mention robotics, but the proposed system could potentially be used in image-guided robotic interventions.
